					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1738398#post-2522251</guid>
				<title>Author&#039;s Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1738398/prelude:primae-formae#post-2522251</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 11 Jun 2016 01:18:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Decibelles</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2005044</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Here's my first serious tale that's been written to completion in over a year. I'm writing some stuff where I'm very much challenging myself to write outside of my comfort zone and in ways and headspaces I never would otherwise. I'll be posting more stuff that's been a challenge for me to write very soon.</p> <p>This is for the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/on-mount-golgotha-hub">On Mount Golgotha canon</a>. You should check it out. This was originally a Christmas exchange gift for <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/vanson" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1991183&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1465608673" alt="Vanson" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1991183)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/vanson" >Vanson</a></span> who has given me permission to post it. This is also my second horror-esque thing that I've written for the site. So nice!</p> <p>Thank you to WrongJohnSilver and psul for looking it over.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Trivia.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Trivia.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <ul> <li>This is the earliest tale set in the OMG canon (thus far), and is meant to show a whole other setting and time period for use in the canon.</li> <li>The lyre here is a very early version of SCP-2458.</li> <li>The score is also a very early version of SCP-012.</li> </ul> </div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Trivia.</a></div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
